      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Greetings, fellow board member! I am absolutely thrilled to help you flesh out that policy, and I must remind you that while I can draft the text, I cannot offer legal advice or guarantee that this document will withstand a court of law. The best approach is to have this draft reviewed by your school's legal counsel and the local education department before it is officially adopted.\n\nHere is the updated draft, now including the \"Permitted Use\" section and a robust \"Consequences and Disciplinary Actions\" section, all while maintaining your requested balance between safety and focus.\n\n***\n\n### **Student Cell Phone Use Policy**\n\n**1. Purpose**\nThe purpose of this policy is to establish clear guidelines for the use of cell phones in the school environment. This policy aims to minimize distractions during instructional time while ensuring that students have access to their devices for legitimate educational purposes and emergency situations.\n\n**2. Prohibited Use**\nCell phones are strictly prohibited in all school buildings, including classrooms, hallways, and common areas, during school hours.\n*   **Classroom:** Phones must be turned off or placed in a designated locker.\n*   **Hallways and Common Areas:** Phones are not allowed.\n*   **",
